ZH: 他穿着一套漂亮的燕尾服去参加晚宴。
EN: He wore a beautiful tailcoat to attend the dinner party.

ZH: 在婚礼上，新郎穿着一套定制的燕尾服，非常帅气。
EN: At the wedding, the groom wore a customized tailcoat, looking very handsome.

ZH: 这件燕尾服是由顶级设计师手工制作的。
EN: This tailcoat was handmade by a top designer.

ZH: 穿上燕尾服可以提升男士的气质。
EN: Wearing a tailcoat can enhance a man's temperament.

ZH: 他的燕尾服上有精美的刺绣图案。
EN: His tailcoat has exquisite embroidery patterns.

ZH: 燕尾服是正式场合的一种传统服装。
EN: Tailcoat is a traditional formal attire for special occasions.

ZH: 燕尾服的前面是短款，后面则是长摆。
EN: The front of the tailcoat is short, while the back is long.

ZH: 这件燕尾服是由优质的面料制成的。
EN: This tailcoat is made of high-quality fabric.

ZH: 燕尾服通常搭配领结和西服裤。
EN: Tailcoats are usually paired with a bowtie and trousers.

ZH: 在英国露天赛马盛会上，观众们经常穿着燕尾服。
EN: At the outdoor horse racing event in England, spectators often wear tailcoats.

ZH: 他花了很多时间挑选一套合适的燕尾服。
EN: He spent a lot of time selecting a suitable tailcoat.

ZH: 节庆活动上，艺人们常常会穿着燕尾服表演。
EN: During festive events, artists often perform in tailcoats.

ZH: 她在一家高级礼服店工作，常常帮客人选购燕尾服。
EN: She works at a high-end formal wear store, often helping customers choose tailcoats.

ZH: 这位演奏家以穿燕尾服而著名。
EN: This musician is famous for wearing a tailcoat.

ZH: 在音乐会上，指挥常常身穿燕尾服。
EN: Conductors often wear tailcoats during concerts.

ZH: 我会在晚宴上穿一套黑色的燕尾服。
EN: I will wear a black tailcoat at the dinner party.

ZH: 燕尾服需要细心熨烫才能保持完美的外观。
EN: Tailcoats need careful ironing to maintain a perfect appearance.

ZH: 这套燕尾服的价格昂贵，只有富人才能买得起。
EN: The price of this tailcoat is expensive, only the wealthy can afford it.

ZH: 他获得奖学金后，去买了一套漂亮的燕尾服。
EN: After receiving the scholarship, he bought a beautiful tailcoat.

ZH: 婚礼当天，新娘舞会上与新郎一起穿着燕尾服。
EN: On the wedding day, the bride also wore a tailcoat with the groom at the dance.
